A 'Sympetrum sanguineum' is a species of dragonfly.
They are known for their bright red color and slender body shape.
They have transparent wings with dark veins running throughout.
The eyes of a 'Sympetrum sanguineum' are large, round, and dark in color.
They can usually be found near freshwater habitats, such as ponds and streams.
Male 'Sympetrum sanguineum' have a reddish-orange abdomen, while females have a brownish-yellow abdomen.
They are a common sight in many parts of Europe and Asia.
